Constructor Detail

BaseRing

public BaseRing(PointCollection pc)
Constructs a ring from a collection of points. BaseRing objects are explicitly closed. If the point collection is not closed, a new closed collection will be created and used by the ring.

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if pc has less than 3 points
See Also:
BasePath.BasePath(PointCollection)

calculateArea

public double calculateArea()
Calculates the vector area of this Ring. Vector area is a signed scalar value. The area of the point collection is positive if the points are anti-clockwise, and negative if clockwise.
